1. ✅ Iterative Stack-Based (Recommended in interviews)

No recursion, no global variables, fully pure.

function flattenArray(arr) {
    const stack = [...arr];
    const result = [];

    while (stack.length) {
        const item = stack.pop();

        if (Array.isArray(item)) {
            stack.push(...item);
        } else {
            result.push(item);
        }
    }

    return result.reverse();
}

const arr = [1, 2, ['a', 'b', [3, 4, [9, ['c', 'd']]]], [5, 6]];

console.log(flattenArray(arr));
Why this is good
❌ no recursion (avoids call stack overflow)
❌ no global variables
❌ no mutation of input
✅ O(n) time
✅ widely used in real systems
